<Base title="About · sound/blog" description="About Liam and this notebook.">
  <section class="about wrap reveal">
    <p class="eyebrow about__kicker">Colophon · Liam Wise</p>
    <h1 class="hero__title">The <em>premise</em>.</h1>

    <div class="prose" style="margin-top: var(--space-6)">
      <p>
        I'm a software engineer and a musician &mdash; two things I've always kept in separate
        rooms. This site is me opening the door between them.
      </p>
      <p>
        The aim, roughly: work at the intersection of music and technology. Tools, infrastructure,
        discovery algorithms, policy-adjacent technical work &mdash; the specific role can emerge
        later. First I need genuine technical depth in audio. DSP, C++, plugin development, and
        eventually music information retrieval, which is the research field sitting under
        streaming discovery.
      </p>
      <p>
        Target: a Masters at UPF's <a href="https://www.upf.edu/web/mtg">Music Technology Group</a>
        in Barcelona, with a thesis in MIR or music discovery. From the end of that program I want
        to be in the right ecosystem with the right skills to actually do something for the
        industry.
      </p>
      <p>
        This site is my public notebook. The writing doubles as a study tool &mdash; I can only
        explain something I really understand &mdash; and as a visible trail. By the time
        applications come around, the work will be on the record.
      </p>
      <p>
        Everything here is in-progress. That's the point.
      </p>

      <hr />

      <p class="eyebrow">Contact</p>
      <p>
        <a href="mailto:wiseliam7@gmail.com">wiseliam7@gmail.com</a> &middot;
        <a href="https://github.com">GitHub</a> &middot;
        <a href="/rss.xml">RSS</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
